	You have to pay attention to variable types!
	int a = 4;
	int b = 3;
	int c = a/b;
	TYPECASTING is a way to change one variable type into another
	You can use typecasting to change integers into float numbers.
	For instance, (float)a will change 4 into 4.0

	float(c) would change c into 1.3 because it's 4/3
    float(c) would change c into 1.0, because the division isn't recalculated

	int d = 5;
	int e = 2;
	float f = (float)d/(float)e;
}
